A study by the University of Calgary revealed that grizzly bears in Banff National Park have the lowest reproductive rate in North America due to human-related deaths.
Efforts to protect the bears have included fenced areas and relocating bears accustomed to humans.
The proposal to remove Yellowstone grizzlies from the endangered species list has sparked controversy.
While some believe the population has recovered, others fear the impact of climate change and habitat loss.
Despite the success story of grizzly bear recovery, environmental groups threaten to sue the government over delisting.
The future of these iconic animals remains uncertain.
